  "prompt": "Has anyone received any call from companies, cut-off of which has been been cleared in LinkedIn Placements Test?",
  "response": "I don't have real-time data or specific updates on individual experiences regarding job placements. However, it is not uncommon for candidates who clear cut-off scores in placement tests, such as those conducted by LinkedIn or other platforms, to receive calls from companies for interview opportunities. These tests often serve as preliminary screening tools, helping companies identify potential candidates for further evaluation.\n\nIf you have cleared the cut-off for such a test, it's advisable to keep your LinkedIn profile up-to-date, actively engage with potential recruiters, and be prepared for possible interview calls. Networking, active job searching, and following up with companies can also increase your chances of receiving opportunities.",
